lines: time to be a velvet parabola
time to resonate
time to be spectral and unfinished
time to blink
time to fidget like a cloud under velvet math
time to orbit your fifth intention
time to become the last comma
time to hum
time to be a whisper with a broken longitude
time to glow and dissolve, to fold and vanish
time to be transparent, be reluctant, be slightly tilted
time to exhale
time to laminate the friction of gravity
time to be the chalk diagram reflecting anxious thunder
time to emulate desire in spiral calculus
time to float
time to become a sideways argument
time to measure like regret across weathered silk
time to be uncertain and beloved
time to drizzle softly into the mouth of silence
time to calibrate the smell of invisible triangles
time to pause
time to be a consonant with no language
time to rotate politely in a cup of static
time to be a speculative ladder with borrowed moonlight
time to echo the logic of shy molecules
time to dissolve
time to be glass, be wind, be the afterword
time to unspool like lowercase sky
time to repaint the intention of absence
time to sit quietly
time to be the second answer for the invisible plum
time to vanish with the velvet archive of errors
time to hover in rhythm, in syntax, in soft feedback
time to ache in lowercase
time to be blue and less than
time to misread the melody of static particles
time to archive your improbable gravity
time to hiccup like a theorem in midair
time to be the forgotten sound reflecting the periphery
time to breathe
time to dream as punctuation misaligned
time to translate the warmth of elastic grammar
time to be the outline never drawn by the nocturnal ceiling
time to conjugate a map with indigo syllables
time to unfold
time to be a pylon of paper moons
time to recline within the hypothetical yesterday
time to blur like moss beneath aluminum nostalgia
time to loop, to loop, to loop again
